OL,3,CCharities and health experts warn
OL,4,Cwelfare cuts could cost lives
OL,6,FA tightening of eligibility for the
OL,7,Fmain disability benefit personal
OL,8,Findependence payment (Pip) and cut to
OL,9,Fthe health element of universal credit
OL,10,F(UC) have prompted stark warnings and
OL,11,Fcalls for a rethink.
OL,13,FChanges to Pip are expected to account
OL,14,Ffor the largest proportion of savings,
OL,15,Fwith the Resolution Foundation think
OL,16,Ftank estimating this could see between
OL,17,F800,000 and 1.2 million people in
OL,18,FEngland and Wales losing support of
OL,19,Fbetween #4,200 and #6,300 per year by
OL,20,Fthe end of the decade.
